<br>
as for &quot;they make enough money&quot;  Who decides that?  Baseball is not an easy sport mind you.. Also it is grueling cause you have to constantly practice and be away from your family. Perhaps more so than anyother sport cause the season is so long. People want to pay lots to see their favorites play but is Alex Rodriguez really worth 25 mil a season to the fans who want to see him?<br>
<br>
Baseball is in need of fixing though.. Even without strikes it has been a dying sport cause of the faster paced action of racing, basketball, football and other sports like them.. People nowadays want action and they feel baseball is boring cause its slow paced.. Also fans of consistantly losing teams have been complaining for years cause they say they can't compete when another team offers tons more money to their players they can't afford to keep. The Royals are a good example cause they had a load of talented offensive stars but had to dump them because they couldn't afford them and are stuck in a losing spiral.. <br>
<br>
While it isnt a given, teams can pay large amounts of money for free agents win a world series and then dump them (Marlins come to mind).  Personally I believe all trades and free agent signings should be better regulated.. No more should a team be able to dump a good player on a team that likes to pay (Yankees) and pick up a buttload of prospects.  <br>
<br>
All trades should be reasonably fair cause when not regulated teams are more likely to push the system.  Also a 100 million payroll tax should be implimented next year and that would increase 20 million every 3 years...I don't like out and out salary caps cause they stagnate a good team. It is very evident in football cause no team has really dominated for a while. The rams are close but one day their players will want too much and they will falter. <p><center>
