<br>
Baseball, basketball, and hockey all have one thing in common.  <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> GUARANTEED CONTRACTS.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  This is something that the most grueling sport of all, <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> AMERICAN FOOTBALL</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END--> does not have.  This is wrong.<br>
<br>
Look at this realistically.  The owners are asking the union to do something that <!--EZCODE BOLD START--><b> NO OTHER COMPANY IN THE WORLD WOULD ASK IT'S EMPLOYEES TO DO, WHICH IS TO SUBJECT THEMSELVES TO LIMITING THE AMOUNT OF MONEY THEY CAN MAKE.</b><!--EZCODE BOLD END-->  I mean seriously, say your boss comes up to you and says, you know, I am willing to pay you 50k a year to do your job, but I want you to take 25k, wouldn't you hold out for more?  That is basically what the baseball owners are doing, they are asking the players to make the owners police themselves.  <br>
<br>
No one held a gun to the owner of the Texas Rangers and forced him to sign A-Rod to a 252 million dollar contract.  He wanted the best player in baseball, and he did what he felt he had to do in order to get him.  If he didn't feel that he could afford it, or make enough off of team revenue to pay for it, then what the fuck was he doing signing the contract???<br>
<br>
If the owners want the players to make decisions on their own salaries, limiting them to the amount they can make, then they need to go into partnership with the players, making them part owners, so that their salaries are linked to the teams they play for.  <br>
<br>
I wish to hell they would just quit bitching, and PLAY FUCKING BASEBALL!!! <p><center><a target="new"href="http://www.magelo.com/eq_view_profile.html?num=30880">Rhes Olooshun - 59th Preserver</a></center>
